name: cred-rea-coral-population-parameters-at-wake-atoll-2005
notes: Belt transects along 1 or 2 consecutively-placed, 25m transect lines were surveyed as part of Rapid Ecological Assessments conducted at 14 sites at Wake Atoll in October, 2005 from the NOAA vessel Oscar Elton Sette (OES05-13). Raw survey data included species presence and relative abundance, colony counts and size classes, and determination of benthic cover using the line-intercept method. One meter on each side of the transect lines were included in the belt (for a total of 50m2 or 100m2 per site), depending on the number of transects surveyed.
